claims:
1. A method, comprising:
a) providing:
i) a subject comprising a plurality of malignant cancer cells;
ii) a P2X7 receptor agonist capable of inducing apoptosis in said cancer cells;

b) administering said agonist to said cancer cells under conditions such that apoptosis is induced.

8. A method, comprising:
a) providing:
i) a subject at risk for developing a plurality of benign cancer cells;
ii) a P2X7 receptor agonist capable of inducing apoptosis in said cancer cells;

b) administering said agonist to said subject under conditions such that apoptosis is induced, thereby preventing the development of said cancer cells.
